content: This is a good app. However, may i suggest that there be a english translation in the rituale, sometimes it will be easier for us to know which text to provide for a particular blessing we want. Thanks.

Each time I upgrade my phone, this app has to charge me a new. I love iMass, can't do without it. Wherever i travel i don't have to carry my missal anymore, and best of all i can get the Mass of the day, Mass location and Divinum Officium. Big Thanks to the creators of this app. Thank you

I am thankful and appreciative for this beautiful App. I do have one constructive suggestion to hopefully improve it. When I pray the Breviarium on my phone, I notice a difference in some of the Latin to English prayer translations (excluding the Psalms) that tend to be more in the vernacular. The translations differ from those found in the 1962 Angelus Press Catholic Daily Missal. The interpretation may be insignificant, but the inconsistency of translation is worrisome. ie; In the Ad Completorium, the Nunc dimittis, Ant.in the phone version: "Protect us Lord while we are awake and safeguard us while we sleep; that we may keep watch with Christ, and rest in peace.' The missal version: "Save us O Lord when we are awake, and keep us while we sleep, that we may watch with Christ and rest in peace" ALSO: In the prayer following the Nunc dimittis, the phone version: "Visit, we beseech thee, O Lord, this dwelling, and drive far from it the snares of the enemy; let thy holy angels dwell herein to preserve us in peace, and let thy blessing be always upon us." The missal version: Visit, we pray thee O Lord, this house, and drive far from it all snares of the enemy. Let Thy holy angels dwell herein to keep us in peace, and may Thy blessing be always upon us. Through our Lord." Notice also the capitalization of "Thy". There are more, but space does not permit. As unimportant as it may seem, inconsistencies result is confusion and misinterpretation. God Bless You.

content: Best and most important app out there, hands down..especially now. I cried watching our priests celebrate mass, alone, during this lockdown. Maybe we all took for granted having our precious Jesus in His Sacraments of Communion, Confession, Baptism, Last Rites, all golden gifts and tools for our salvation. This app is a blessed gift and spiritual life line we cannot afford to pass up. The doors of our churches are shut, but here we can soberly celebrate at home with this technology.

replyContent: Our policy is the acceptance of the local Catholic Diocese or Archdiocese. When in doubt we contact the local Diocese offices to ask if a location is approved for Catholic attendance. If your location is not approved by their local Diocese have them contact the Diocese to see how they can get faculties.
